{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T08:10:06.355Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dropout Mechanism"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a regularization technique that randomly deactivates (drops out) a subset of neurons during training by setting their outputs to zero. This forces the network to learn robust, redundant features and prevents "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "co-adaptation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (over-reliance on specific neurons), significantly reducing overfitting in deep neural networks."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Dropout Mechanism — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Dropout Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "During training, dropout temporarily removes neurons from the network:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "For each training iteration"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", randomly select a fraction of neurons to drop"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Set their outputs to zero"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (both forward and backward pass)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scale remaining neurons"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to maintain expected activation values"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Repeat"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with different random neurons each iteration"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dropout rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " ("}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "r_d"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "): The fraction of neurons to drop (common values: 0.2–0.5)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Dropout Matters: The Problem It Solves"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Co-Adaptation Problem"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When a layer has many neurons, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "co-adaptation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " occurs:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multiple neurons learn "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "similar features"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (redundant)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Connection weights become nearly identical"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Neurons become "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "overly reliant"}, {"type": "text", "text": " on each other"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Network memorizes training data instead of learning general patterns"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Excellent training performance, poor test performance → "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "overfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dropout's Solution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dropout "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "breaks co-adaptation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " by:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Randomly silencing neurons → network can't rely on specific neurons"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Forces each neuron to contribute "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "meaningfully on its own"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Creates "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "redundancy"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → multiple pathways to learn features"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prevents rigid pathways that fail when conditions change"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Dropout Works: Step-by-Step"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training Phase"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input layer: [0.5, 0.8, 0.3, 0.9, 0.2, 0.7]  (6 neurons)\nDropout rate: 1/3 (~33%)\n\nStep 1: Generate dropout mask\nMask: [1, 0, 1, 1, 0, 1]  (randomly keep/drop)\n\nStep 2: Apply mask (element-wise multiply)\nDropped: [0.5, 0, 0.3, 0.9, 0, 0.7]\n\nStep 3: Scale remaining neurons (inverted dropout)\nScale factor: 1 / (1 - 1/3) = 1.5\nOutput: [0.75, 0, 0.45, 1.35, 0, 1.05]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Scaling ensures "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "expected activation value remains the same"}, {"type": "text", "text": " whether dropout is applied or not."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inverted Dropout (Standard Implementation)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The most common dropout variant:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Create mask"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with values 1 (keep) or 0 (drop) based on keep rate"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Element-wise multiply"}, {"type": "text", "text": " mask with activations (zeros out dropped neurons)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Divide by keep rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to scale up remaining neurons"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why inverted?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " - Scaling during training → no adjustment needed at test time\n- Keeps network behavior "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "consistent"}, {"type": "text", "text": " between training and testing"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visual Example: Dropout at Multiple Training Steps"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Layer with 6 units, dropout rate = 1/3:\n\nTraining step 1:\n  Original: [0.5, 0.8, 0.3, 0.9, 0.2, 0.7]\n  Mask:     [1,  0,  1,  1,  0,  1]\n  Output:   [0.75, 0, 0.45, 1.35, 0, 1.05]  ← neurons 2,5 dropped\n\nTraining step 2:\n  Original: [0.5, 0.8, 0.3, 0.9, 0.2, 0.7]\n  Mask:     [0,  1,  1,  0,  1,  1]\n  Output:   [0, 1.2, 0.45, 0, 0.3, 1.05]  ← neurons 1,4 dropped (different!)\n\nTraining step 3:\n  Original: [0.5, 0.8, 0.3, 0.9, 0.2, 0.7]\n  Mask:     [1,  1,  0,  1,  1,  0]\n  Output:   [0.75, 1.2, 0, 1.35, 0.3, 0]  ← neurons 3,6 dropped (different again!)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key benefit"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Different \"thinner network\" changes on every iteration → approximates training "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "many different sub-networks"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Testing/Inference Phase: Dropout Behavior"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Happens During Testing"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Phase"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dropout Applied?"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scaling?"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes (randomly drop neurons)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes (divide by keep rate)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Testing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ No (all neurons active)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ No (no adjustment needed)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why no dropout at test time?"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Avoid introducing randomness into predictions\n- Ensure outputs are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "stable, reliable, deterministic"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Inverted dropout scaling during training → no test-time adjustment needed"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Dropout Works: The Mechanisms"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Ensemble of Sub-Networks"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dropout trains "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "many different smaller networks"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that share weights:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each iteration uses a different subset of neurons"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effectively trains ~2ⁿ sub-networks (where n = number of neurons)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "At test time, full network approximates "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "averaging all sub-networks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Analogy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Like training 100 different models and averaging their predictions → better generalization."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Prevents Co-Adaptation"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "By randomly removing neurons:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Network can't rely on specific neuron combinations"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each neuron learns "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "robust, independent features"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reduces dependencies between neurons"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Shrinks Weight Norms"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dropout has implicit "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L2 regularization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " effect:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Forces weights to shrink (smaller squared norm)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smaller weights → less overfitting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. Adds Noise (Regularization)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Random dropout introduces "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "stochasticity"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Similar to data augmentation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Makes network more robust to variations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dropout vs. Other Regularization Methods"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Method"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Works"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pros"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cons"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dropout"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Randomly drop neurons during training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Simple, effective, no weight penalties"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slower training (2-3×), needs more epochs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L1 Regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Penalize sum of absolute weights"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sparsity (some weights = 0)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can underfit if too strong"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L2 Regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Penalize sum of squared weights"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smooth weight decay"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Doesn't create sparsity"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Norm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Normalize layer inputs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stabilizes training, acts as regularizer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch size dependency, doesn't replace dropout completely"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key difference"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Dropout is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "implicit regularization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (no explicit penalty on weights), while L1/L2 are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "explicit regularization"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Dropout"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommendation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical Rate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fully-connected layers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use dropout"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (standard)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.5 (50%)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CNN convolutional layers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "⚠️ Optional (Batch Norm often sufficient)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.2–0.3"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CNN pooling layers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ Don't use (rare)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "N/A"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use dropout"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (after attention, FFN)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.1–0.2"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "RNNs/LSTMs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use dropout"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (on non-recurrent connections)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.2–0.5"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule of thumb"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Large, fully-connected networks → high dropout (0.5)\n- Convolutional networks → lower dropout or skip (Batch Norm handles regularization)\n- Transformers → moderate dropout (0.1–0.2)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practical Implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn as nn\n\nmodel = nn.Sequential(\n    nn.Linear(128, 256),\n    nn.Dropout(0.5),  # 50% dropout\n    nn.ReLU(),\n    nn.Linear(256, 128),\n    nn.Dropout(0.5),\n    nn.ReLU(),\n    nn.Linear(128, 10)\n)\n\n# Training\nmodel.train()  # Dropout active\noutput = model(x)\n\n# Testing\nmodel.eval()   # Dropout disabled\noutput = model(x)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from tensorflow.keras import layers, models\n\nmodel = models.Sequential([\n    layers.Dense(256, input_shape=(128,)),\n    layers.Dropout(0.5),  # 50% dropout\n    layers.ReLU(),\n    layers.Dense(128),\n    layers.Dropout(0.5),\n    layers.ReLU(),\n    layers.Dense(10)\n])\n\n# Training: Dropout automatically active\nmodel.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=10)\n\n# Testing: Dropout automatically disabled\npredictions = model.predict(x_test)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Mistakes and Pitfalls"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Using dropout at test time"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Random, unstable predictions"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "model.eval()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in PyTorch"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dropout on CNN conv layers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can hurt performance (Batch Norm better)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use dropout on Dense layers only"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Too high dropout rate (>0.5)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Network underfits (can't learn)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start with 0.5, tune down if needed"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Too low dropout rate (<0.1)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No regularization effect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use 0.2–0.5 for most cases"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not training long enough"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dropout slows convergence (2-3×)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Train more epochs when using dropout"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dropout"}, {"type": "text", "text": " randomly deactivates neurons during training → prevents overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Co-adaptation problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Neurons become over-reliant on each other → dropout breaks this"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Inverted dropout"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Scale remaining neurons during training → no adjustment at test time"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Apply dropout (random mask + scaling)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Testing"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": All neurons active, no dropout → deterministic predictions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Works by"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Training ensemble of sub-networks, preventing co-adaptation, shrinking weight norms"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Typical rates"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 0.5 for Dense layers, 0.1–0.3 for CNNs/Transformers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Slower training"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 2-3× more epochs needed vs. no dropout"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Implicit regularizer"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": No explicit weight penalty (unlike L1/L2)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dropout is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "simple yet powerful regularization technique"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that has become a staple in deep learning, helping models achieve better generalization by reducing overfitting through randomized neuron deactivation."}]}]}}